# Compound-edge bridge: relays every kind onto the enclosing compound's
# `out { output: Egress }` port. Inner pipelines that end in
# packet-shaped primitives (Counter, Buffer, Service…) can't emit
# `to out` themselves — they emit `to default`, which only sees direct
# outbound edges. Wiring `… -> Egress` then declaring the compound's
# `out { output: Egress }` lets the pipeline cross the compound
# boundary without modifying any primitive.
#
# Convention: every composite that needs an output port uses
# `out { output: Egress }` and routes its final stage into Egress.
# (`out` is a reserved keyword so we can't name the port `out`.)
#
# One rule handles every kind by binding the whole packet and
# re-emitting it verbatim. Previously this was 7 per-variant rules.
node Egress {
    rule fwd { on p do { emit p to out output } }
}
